# Keep the Docker build context small. Without this, the whole repository
# (.git, build outputs, MonacoEditor, binaries...) is packed and sent to the
# Docker daemon on every build, which is very slow.
#
# The web image only needs three files, none of which match the excludes below:
#   server/docker/web/artifacts/linux64/repwebexe
#   server/docker/web/scripts/docker-entrypoint.sh
#   repman/dbxdrivers.ini

.git
.github
build
getit
reportmand7
MonacoEditor
**/node_modules
**/__history
**/__recovery

# Compiler / IDE output directories
**/bin32
**/bin64
**/binr32
**/binr64
**/binl64
**/binrl64
**/dcu32
**/dcu64
**/dcur32
**/dcur64
**/dcurl64
**/dculinux64
**/dcurlinux64

# Heavy / irrelevant file types for the image
**/*.exe
**/*.dll
**/*.bpl
**/*.dcp
**/*.dcu
**/*.o
**/*.obj
**/*.a
**/*.lib
**/*.zip
**/*.7z
**/*.rar
**/*.tlb
**/*.pdf
**/*.png
**/*.jpg
**/*.jpeg
**/*.gif
**/*.ico

# The large Linux self-hosted binary in server/web is NOT the one the image
# uses (the image uses server/docker/web/artifacts/linux64/repwebexe).
server/web/repwebexe
